<item>
            <title>[AVRO-1710] sync() returns wrong value if DataFileWriter.appendTo() is used to initialize the DataFileWriter</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-1710</link>
                <project id="12310911" key="AVRO">Apache Avro</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If you append to an existing file using DataFileWriter.appendTo(), sync() returns the wrong values as it doesn&apos;t take into account the position in the existing file.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12849630">AVRO-1710</key>
            <summary>sync() returns wrong value if DataFileWriter.appendTo() is used to initialize the DataFileWriter</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
